I notice there are no nameservers for the navy.mil domain.
Apparently the root servers don't delegate navy.mil, but
rather delegate the next level down; eg, usna.navy.mil.

&gt;From RFC1034 I gather this is okay; ie, the root servers
have an SOA for mil, and no NS records "in between".

&gt;From RFC1033 (the SRI.COM example) I gather it's would have
been okay for the root servers to include SOA and NS records
for navy.mil, listing themselves.

Is there any reason to prefer one way over the other; ie,
given that a server will be authoritative for both a domain
(mil) and subdomain (navy.mil), is there any reason to include
SOA and NS records for the subdomain?

Thanks,

Ron Stanonik
stanonik@nprdc.arpa

